flavor_text_entries.diamond:
It loves the honey of flowers
and steals honey collected by
COMBEE.
flavor_text_entries.pearl:
It does not keep a nest. It flies
over fields and mountains in
constant search of floral honey.
flavor_text_entries.platinum:
While it loves floral honey, it won’t
gather any itself. Instead, it
plots to steal some from COMBEE.
flavor_text_entries.heartgold:
It flutters around at night and
steals honey from the COMBEE hive.

flavor_text_entries.legends-arceus:
Scatters steel-colored scales as it flaps its wings. Despite
being observed feeding primarily on the nectar of flowers,
Mothim is not often seen around flower gardens.
